I have learned that love is the nuclear strength word for acceptance.  I have found love on this site..for me.. and I have found something else very important to me.. I have found someone to love.  I need to work on loving myself.. genuine love.. not ego mania, vanity, conceit, arrogance..etc.  Then I will be better able to love others beyond superficial veneers.<br>
I have never been able to do that except with dead guys. Now I have learned to love a few on this site.. simple, unconditional, brotherly love...a kind of love that is called for in the &quot;White Horse Song&quot;(a tough standard).. a love that naturally incorporates respect, loyalty, devotion, concern and an expectation of reciprocation...and the expectation has been fulfilled.  My brothers on this site have been the greatest gift to me since the birth of my children.  They are sacred.<br>
If these few men of honor can love, forgive, and accept me, then there is a good possibility that I can do the same.<br><br>
The road is long, but longer if you get lost.<br><br>
I don't know who you are William Donald.  But, I don't like your mechanical statement, &quot;Enough with the roads, and the warriors, and the similary overwrought metaphors........&quot;<br>
Also, I don't like your bold and aggressive line of questioning.  If you want to force feed your instant clinical bullshit or test your theory, I suggest you go back to the student lounge or retake &quot;counseling process 101.&quot;  This site is not a gold fish bowl for novice marine biologist to drool into.  Cut the bullshit and submit your own views and feelings.  If you know anything about the group process.. you will make yourself known and accepted first, then you may interact.<br>
Also, take your statement, &quot;We're neither as good nor as bad as we'd hoped and feared, now and then&quot; to some creative writing professor who just might be able to figure out what you mean.  If he can't figure it out.. he'll probably give you an &quot;A&quot;!<br><br>
